A book weak-two bid from Casen had Brogeland quietly entering
the auction with 3C on his enormous black-hand. Schwartz countered
with a fit-showing-jump to 4D. He certainly had the red suits!
Erichsen took the opportunity to introduce his spades, and all
of a sudden Brogeland's hand became gigantic. He advanced with
a 5D cue-bid, and Schwartz bid what he thought his side could
make - 5H. Exactly what Erichsen's 6D is all about - you will
have to ask him. Brogeland gave it one more try with a sort of
"last train" 6H call. Great bid.
}
