A fairly standard non-vulnerable preempt from Brogeland in first
chair. This silenced everyone, which was just as well for E/W
since a spade contract would suffer six losers with the heart
ruff. Erichsen was a spade stopper away from 3NT, though there
was a slight chance of 3NT making on a non-spade lead. Imagine
that North did try 3NT, and East had to lead. The DA or a spade
lead would defeat 3NT - assuming a spade shift after the DA -
but, all other leads allow the questionable game to make. Is
there any cachet in attempting 3NT with the North cards?
